The paper discusses a modification to the LSTM and GRU architectures, which are commonly used in neural networks for temporal sequence problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents empirical results showing improved performance, indicating that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper deals with memory and sequence processing, which could also place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
